## Quick Reference: Adding a Feature

### New API Endpoint
1. Add route in `server/src/routes/*.routes.js`
2. Add service method in `server/src/services/*.service.js`
3. Add validation in `server/src/middleware/validation.js` if needed
4. Register route in `server/src/app.js`
5. Add client API method in `client/src/services/api.js`

### New Client Page
1. Create component in `client/src/<Feature>/`
2. Add route in `client/src/main.jsx`
3. Add Navbar link in `client/src/components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx` if needed
4. Use `useApi()` hook for API calls
5. Access auth via `useContext(AuthContext)`

### DB Migration
1. Modify `server/db/schema.sql`
2. Apply changes to AWS RDS instance manually
3. Update corresponding service queries
